div.p:
F-statistics of hierarchical structuring of genetic variance. Relationship between hierarchy levels are indicated in rows with ‘/’ indicating ‘within’; 
Hierarchy A: 3 migratory directions (NW, SW, SE) and 3 migratory distances (short-, intermediate-, long-distance) with the 
Os population characterized having SW migratory direction (dir); 
Hierarchy B: 3 migratory directions (NW, SW, SE) and 3 migratory distances (short-, intermediate-, long-distance) with the 
Os population characterized having SE migratory direction (dir).
